  "texts": [
    "{\"estimated_metrics\": \"total distance: 8.3m, estimated time: 61s, energy consumption: 21.6Wh\" } Required Monitoring: This section defines the aspects of the system that must be continuously monitored to ensure safe and efficient task execution.",
    "{\"required_monitoring\": \"object tracking, force feedback, obstacle detection, battery level\" }The task plan generation process can be formally defined as:ERCP = f (c, A, T),where:• c is the user command,• A is the set of action primitives (APIs),• T is the set of textual clarifications and context.",
    "The Embodied Robotic Control Prompt (ERCP) is then used as input to the Large Language Model (LLM) to generate the task plan:P = LLM(ERCP, θ),V (p i, S, S ′) = 1 if p i satisfies all constraints in state S ′, 0 otherwise, where:• p i: A placeholder in the task plan,• S: Initial environmental state,• S ′: Environmental state incorporating real-time sensor updates.",
    "The task plan is executed only if V (p i, S, S ′) = 1 for all placeholders.",
    "If verification fails during the initial validation, the task is not executed."
